	<item>
		<title>Sample Page</title>
		<link>http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook-wordpress/demo-1/sample-page/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Dec 2015 06:53:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[eriktailor]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook-wordpress/demo-1/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

<blockquote>Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>

...or something like this:

<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>

As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook-wordpress/demo-1/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>2</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date><![CDATA[2015-12-08 06:53:39]]></wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt><![CDATA[2015-12-08 06:53:39]]></wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status><![CDATA[closed]]></wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status><![CDATA[open]]></wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name><![CDATA[sample-page]]></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status><![CDATA[trash]]></wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type><![CDATA[page]]></wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password><![CDATA[]]></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
		<wp:postmeta>
			<wp:meta_key><![CDATA[_wp_page_template]]></wp:meta_key>
			<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[default]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
		<wp:postmeta>
			<wp:meta_key><![CDATA[_wp_trash_meta_time]]></wp:meta_key>
			<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[1449559583]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>Sample Page</title>
		<link>http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook-wordpress/demo-1/sample-page-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 20 Nov 2015 16:43:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[eriktailor]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook/demo-1/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

<blockquote>Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>

...or something like this:

<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>

As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://demo.eriktailor.com/flatbook/demo-1/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Aliquam erat volutpat. Duis viverra at erat ut semper. In purus nisl, luctus sed eleifend at, pellentesque ut dolor. Nunc sodales nisi sed ullamcorper pellentesque. Etiam posuere nulla eu lectus porta ullamcorper. Aenean sit amet lectus eget augue euismod ultricies eu nec risus.<!--more-->

Nullam at fringilla mi, vitae congue purus. Proin lacinia lorem in felis mollis volutpat. Suspendisse scelerisque turpis quis est scelerisque finibus. Vivamus aliquam at sem eu laoreet. Sed finibus faucibus enim, quis faucibus ante gravida quis. Mauris ornare, enim a venenatis cursus, nisl quam aliquam justo, a ultrices nibh lectus semper felis. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Pellentesque auctor faucibus turpis, id laoreet lacus facilisis et. Sed eu purus blandit, iaculis elit nec, feugiat dolor. Cras blandit euismod finibus. Quisque et sodales ante, sit amet tincidunt enim. Aliquam mattis vel dui id scelerisque. Ut elementum vel massa et bibendum. Suspendisse potenti. Curabitur pharetra congue turpis, sagittis ultrices tellus hendrerit vulputate. Vestibulum tristique laoreet nisl, eu condimentum purus auctor at.
